[
  {
    "text": "Alexios Komnenos,",
    "start": 7.071,
    "duration": 1.92
  },
  {
    "text": "Byzantine emperor,",
    "start": 8.991,
    "duration": 1.38
  },
  {
    "text": "led his army to meet the Scythian hordes",
    "start": 10.371,
    "duration": 2.675
  },
  {
    "text": "in battle.",
    "start": 13.046,
    "duration": 1.065
  },
  {
    "text": "For good luck,",
    "start": 14.111,
    "duration": 1.16
  },
  {
    "text": "he carried one of the holiest relics",
    "start": 15.271,
    "duration": 1.99
  },
  {
    "text": "in Christendom:",
    "start": 17.261,
    "duration": 1.12
  },
  {
    "text": "the veil that had belonged",
    "start": 18.381,
    "duration": 1.37
  },
  {
    "text": "to the Virgin Mary.",
    "start": 19.751,
    "duration": 1.97
  },
  {
    "text": "Unfortunately, it didn’t help.",
    "start": 21.731,
    "duration": 2.3
  },
  {
    "text": "Not only was his army defeated,",
    "start": 24.031,
    "duration": 2.25
  },
  {
    "text": "but as they fled,",
    "start": 26.281,
    "duration": 1.21
  },
  {
    "text": "the Emperor was stabbed in the buttocks.",
    "start": 27.491,
    "duration": 2.74
  },
  {
    "text": "To make matters worse, a strong wind",
    "start": 30.249,
    "duration": 2.38
  },
  {
    "text": "made the relic too heavy to carry,",
    "start": 32.629,
    "duration": 2.27
  },
  {
    "text": "so he stashed it in some bushes",
    "start": 34.899,
    "duration": 1.75
  },
  {
    "text": "as he escaped.",
    "start": 36.649,
    "duration": 1.356
  },
  {
    "text": "But even as he fled,",
    "start": 38.005,
    "duration": 1.41
  },
  {
    "text": "he managed to slay some Scythians",
    "start": 39.415,
    "duration": 2.1
  },
  {
    "text": "and rescue a few comrades.",
    "start": 41.515,
    "duration": 2.68
  },
  {
    "text": "At least, this is how Alexios' daughter",
    "start": 44.195,
    "duration": 2.99
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna recounted the story,",
    "start": 47.185,
    "duration": 1.85
  },
  {
    "text": "writing nearly 60 years later.",
    "start": 49.035,
    "duration": 2.74
  },
  {
    "text": "She spent the last decade of her long life",
    "start": 51.775,
    "duration": 2.99
  },
  {
    "text": "creating a 500-page history",
    "start": 54.765,
    "duration": 2.5
  },
  {
    "text": "of her father’s reign called The Alexiad.",
    "start": 57.265,
    "duration": 2.88
  },
  {
    "text": "Written in Greek, the book was modeled",
    "start": 60.145,
    "duration": 1.92
  },
  {
    "text": "after ancient Greek epics",
    "start": 62.065,
    "duration": 1.65
  },
  {
    "text": "and historical writings.",
    "start": 63.715,
    "duration": 1.7
  },
  {
    "text": "But Anna had a different, trickier task",
    "start": 65.415,
    "duration": 2.45
  },
  {
    "text": "than the writers in these traditions:",
    "start": 67.865,
    "duration": 2.19
  },
  {
    "text": "as a princess writing",
    "start": 70.055,
    "duration": 1.11
  },
  {
    "text": "about her own family,",
    "start": 71.165,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "she had to balance her loyalty to her kin",
    "start": 72.625,
    "duration": 2.59
  },
  {
    "text": "with her obligation",
    "start": 75.215,
    "duration": 1.24
  },
  {
    "text": "to portray events accurately,",
    "start": 76.455,
    "duration": 2.26
  },
  {
    "text": "navigating issues like Alexios’s",
    "start": 78.715,
    "duration": 2.44
  },
  {
    "text": "embarrassing stab to the buttocks.",
    "start": 81.155,
    "duration": 2.42
  },
  {
    "text": "A lifetime of study and participation",
    "start": 83.575,
    "duration": 2.18
  },
  {
    "text": "in her father’s government",
    "start": 85.755,
    "duration": 1.35
  },
  {
    "text": "prepared Anna for this undertaking.",
    "start": 87.105,
    "duration": 3.0
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna was born in 1083,",
    "start": 90.112,
    "duration": 2.52
  },
  {
    "text": "shortly after her father seized control",
    "start": 92.632,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "of the Roman Empire",
    "start": 94.912,
    "duration": 1.4
  },
  {
    "text": "following a decade of brutal civil wars",
    "start": 96.312,
    "duration": 2.66
  },
  {
    "text": "and revolts.",
    "start": 98.972,
    "duration": 1.55
  },
  {
    "text": "The empire was deep in decline",
    "start": 100.522,
    "duration": 1.844
  },
  {
    "text": "when he came to power,",
    "start": 102.366,
    "duration": 1.31
  },
  {
    "text": "and threatened from all sides:",
    "start": 103.676,
    "duration": 1.94
  },
  {
    "text": "by the Seljuk Turks in the East,",
    "start": 105.616,
    "duration": 2.05
  },
  {
    "text": "the Normans in the West,",
    "start": 107.666,
    "duration": 1.89
  },
  {
    "text": "and Scythian raiders to the north.",
    "start": 109.556,
    "duration": 2.32
  },
  {
    "text": "Over the course of Anna’s childhood",
    "start": 111.876,
    "duration": 2.04
  },
  {
    "text": "and adolescence,",
    "start": 113.916,
    "duration": 1.13
  },
  {
    "text": "Alexios fought constant military campaigns",
    "start": 115.046,
    "duration": 2.72
  },
  {
    "text": "to secure the frontiers of his empire,",
    "start": 117.766,
    "duration": 2.54
  },
  {
    "text": "even striking up an uneasy alliance",
    "start": 120.306,
    "duration": 2.12
  },
  {
    "text": "with the Crusaders.",
    "start": 122.426,
    "duration": 1.94
  },
  {
    "text": "Meanwhile in Constantinople,",
    "start": 124.366,
    "duration": 2.224
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna fought her own battle.",
    "start": 126.59,
    "duration": 2.08
  },
  {
    "text": "She was expected to study subjects",
    "start": 128.67,
    "duration": 2.02
  },
  {
    "text": "considered proper",
    "start": 130.69,
    "duration": 1.08
  },
  {
    "text": "for a Byzantine princess,",
    "start": 131.77,
    "duration": 1.87
  },
  {
    "text": "like courtly etiquette and the Bible,",
    "start": 133.64,
    "duration": 2.35
  },
  {
    "text": "but preferred classical myth",
    "start": 135.99,
    "duration": 1.68
  },
  {
    "text": "and philosophy.",
    "start": 137.67,
    "duration": 1.29
  },
  {
    "text": "To access this material, she had to learn",
    "start": 138.96,
    "duration": 2.523
  },
  {
    "text": "to read and speak Ancient Greek,",
    "start": 141.483,
    "duration": 2.47
  },
  {
    "text": "by studying secretly at night.",
    "start": 143.953,
    "duration": 2.46
  },
  {
    "text": "Eventually her parents realized",
    "start": 146.413,
    "duration": 1.52
  },
  {
    "text": "how serious she was,",
    "start": 147.933,
    "duration": 1.29
  },
  {
    "text": "and provided her with tutors.",
    "start": 149.223,
    "duration": 2.18
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna expanded her studies",
    "start": 151.403,
    "duration": 1.53
  },
  {
    "text": "to classical literature, rhetoric,",
    "start": 152.933,
    "duration": 2.26
  },
  {
    "text": "history, philosophy, mathematics,",
    "start": 155.193,
    "duration": 2.9
  },
  {
    "text": "astronomy, and medicine.",
    "start": 158.093,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "One scholar even complained",
    "start": 160.093,
    "duration": 1.65
  },
  {
    "text": "that her constant requests",
    "start": 161.743,
    "duration": 1.25
  },
  {
    "text": "for more Aristotle commentaries",
    "start": 162.993,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "were wearing out his eyes.",
    "start": 164.793,
    "duration": 2.36
  },
  {
    "text": "At age fifteen,",
    "start": 167.153,
    "duration": 1.04
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna married Nikephoros Bryennios",
    "start": 168.193,
    "duration": 2.59
  },
  {
    "text": "to quell old conflicts",
    "start": 170.783,
    "duration": 1.5
  },
  {
    "text": "between their families",
    "start": 172.283,
    "duration": 1.08
  },
  {
    "text": "and strengthen Alexios’s reign.",
    "start": 173.363,
    "duration": 2.43
  },
  {
    "text": "Fortunately, Anna and Nikephoros ended up",
    "start": 175.793,
    "duration": 2.81
  },
  {
    "text": "sharing many intellectual interests,",
    "start": 178.603,
    "duration": 2.21
  },
  {
    "text": "hosting and debating",
    "start": 180.813,
    "duration": 1.31
  },
  {
    "text": "the leading scholars of the day.",
    "start": 182.123,
    "duration": 2.42
  },
  {
    "text": "Meanwhile, Alexios’s military excursions",
    "start": 184.543,
    "duration": 3.13
  },
  {
    "text": "began to pay off,",
    "start": 187.673,
    "duration": 1.39
  },
  {
    "text": "restoring many of the empire’s",
    "start": 189.063,
    "duration": 1.83
  },
  {
    "text": "former territories.",
    "start": 190.893,
    "duration": 1.68
  },
  {
    "text": "As her father aged,",
    "start": 192.573,
    "duration": 1.41
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna and her husband helped her parents",
    "start": 193.983,
    "duration": 2.37
  },
  {
    "text": "with their imperial duties.",
    "start": 196.353,
    "duration": 2.07
  },
  {
    "text": "During this time,",
    "start": 198.423,
    "duration": 1.15
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna reportedly advocated for",
    "start": 199.573,
    "duration": 1.59
  },
  {
    "text": "just treatment of the people",
    "start": 201.163,
    "duration": 1.65
  },
  {
    "text": "in their disputes with the government.",
    "start": 202.813,
    "duration": 2.42
  },
  {
    "text": "After Alexios’s death,",
    "start": 205.233,
    "duration": 2.04
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna’s brother John ascended to the throne",
    "start": 207.273,
    "duration": 2.4
  },
  {
    "text": "and Anna turned back",
    "start": 209.673,
    "duration": 1.25
  },
  {
    "text": "to philosophy and scholarship.",
    "start": 210.923,
    "duration": 2.01
  },
  {
    "text": "Her husband had written a history",
    "start": 212.933,
    "duration": 1.85
  },
  {
    "text": "arguing that his grandfather",
    "start": 214.783,
    "duration": 1.76
  },
  {
    "text": "would have made a better emperor",
    "start": 216.543,
    "duration": 1.64
  },
  {
    "text": "than Alexios,",
    "start": 218.183,
    "duration": 1.24
  },
  {
    "text": "but Anna disagreed.",
    "start": 219.423,
    "duration": 1.91
  },
  {
    "text": "She began working on the Alexiad,",
    "start": 221.333,
    "duration": 1.97
  },
  {
    "text": "which made the case for her father's",
    "start": 223.303,
    "duration": 1.76
  },
  {
    "text": "merits as emperor.",
    "start": 225.063,
    "duration": 1.99
  },
  {
    "text": "Spanning the late 11th and early 12th",
    "start": 227.053,
    "duration": 2.429
  },
  {
    "text": "centuries of Byzantine history,",
    "start": 229.482,
    "duration": 1.85
  },
  {
    "text": "the Alexiad recounts",
    "start": 231.332,
    "duration": 1.32
  },
  {
    "text": "the tumultuous events of Alexios’s reign,",
    "start": 232.652,
    "duration": 3.09
  },
  {
    "text": "and Anna’s own reactions to those events,",
    "start": 235.742,
    "duration": 2.97
  },
  {
    "text": "like bursting into tears at the thought",
    "start": 238.712,
    "duration": 1.9
  },
  {
    "text": "of the deaths of her parents and husband.",
    "start": 240.612,
    "duration": 2.98
  },
  {
    "text": "She may have included \nthese emotional passages",
    "start": 243.592,
    "duration": 2.2
  },
  {
    "text": "in hopes that they would make her writing",
    "start": 245.792,
    "duration": 1.98
  },
  {
    "text": "more palatable to a society",
    "start": 247.772,
    "duration": 1.76
  },
  {
    "text": "that believed women shouldn't",
    "start": 249.532,
    "duration": 1.38
  },
  {
    "text": "write about battles and empires.",
    "start": 250.912,
    "duration": 2.6
  },
  {
    "text": "While her loyalty to her father",
    "start": 253.512,
    "duration": 1.702
  },
  {
    "text": "was evident in her favorable account",
    "start": 255.214,
    "duration": 1.85
  },
  {
    "text": "of his reign, she also included criticism",
    "start": 257.064,
    "duration": 2.64
  },
  {
    "text": "and her opinions of events.",
    "start": 259.704,
    "duration": 2.58
  },
  {
    "text": "In the centuries after her death,",
    "start": 262.284,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna’s Alexiad was copied over and over,",
    "start": 264.18,
    "duration": 2.73
  },
  {
    "text": "and remains an invaluable",
    "start": 266.91,
    "duration": 1.74
  },
  {
    "text": "eyewitness account",
    "start": 268.65,
    "duration": 1.15
  },
  {
    "text": "of Alexios’s reign today.",
    "start": 269.8,
    "duration": 2.63
  },
  {
    "text": "And through her epic historical narrative,",
    "start": 272.43,
    "duration": 2.49
  },
  {
    "text": "Anna Komnene secured",
    "start": 274.92,
    "duration": 1.57
  },
  {
    "text": "her own place in history.",
    "start": 276.49,
    "duration": 2.75
  }
]